  "texts": [
    "Solving the Self-Consistent Mean-Field Equations Outline of the Iterative ProcedureIn order to find a density matrix P that satisfies the self-consistency condition, the basic procedure is as follows.",
    "24 We caution that sometimes this is defined instead as P ab = ⟨ĉ † a ĉb ⟩, such as in the companion codes.",
    "25 One way to motivate this definition is to consider a \"partial Wick contraction\" given by ĉ †a ĉ † b ĉd ĉc → ⟨ĉ † a ĉc ⟩ ĉ † b ĉd + ⟨ĉ † b ĉd ⟩ ĉ † a ĉc -⟨ĉ † a ĉd ⟩ ĉ † b ĉc -⟨ĉ † b ĉc ⟩ ĉ †a ĉd.",
    "This is the mathematical way of expressing the notion that every electron experiences the mean-field generated by the other electrons.",
    "26 We emphasize the presence of the factor of 1 2 in front of the Hartree and Fock terms."
  ]
}